<!-- FAQ ───────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="section section-muted">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row align-items-start g-5">
            <div class="col-lg-4 animate-on-scroll">
                <div class="section-tag"><i class="bi bi-question-circle"></i> FAQ</div>
                <h2 class="section-title">Frequently asked questions</h2>
                <p class="section-subtitle">
                    Can't find your answer here? <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="Faq" style="color:#5865f2;font-weight:600;">View all FAQs</a> or reach out to our support team.
                </p>
                <a asp-controller="Account" asp-action="Register" class="btn-hero-primary d-inline-flex mt-2">
                    Get started free <i class="bi bi-arrow-right"></i>
                </a>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-8 animate-on-scroll" style="transition-delay:0.1s">
                <div class="accordion faq-accordion" id="faqAccordion">
                    <div class="accordion-item">
                        <h2 class="accordion-header">
                            <button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq1">
                                How do I import my contacts?
                            </button>
                        </h2>
                        <div id="faq1" class="accordion-collapse collapse show" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                            <div class="accordion-body">
                                Upload a standard .xlsx or .csv file from the Contacts section. MailTo will guide you through mapping columns to contact fields — the whole process takes under two minutes.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="accordion-item">
                        <h2 class="accordion-header">
                            <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq2">
                                Can I use my own email server (SMTP)?
                            </button>
                        </h2>
                        <div id="faq2" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                            <div class="accordion-body">
                                Yes. Add any SMTP configuration — Gmail, Outlook, SendGrid, Amazon SES, or your own server. You can store multiple SMTP profiles and pick one per campaign.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="accordion-item">
                        <h2 class="accordion-header">
                            <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq3">
                                How does email personalisation work?
                            </button>
                        </h2>
                        <div id="faq3" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                            <div class="accordion-body">
                                Define custom fields when importing your contacts, then use merge tags in your email template body. MailTo replaces each tag with the real value before sending to each recipient.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="accordion-item">
                        <h2 class="accordion-header">
                            <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq4">
                                Can I track who opened my emails?
                            </button>
                        </h2>
                        <div id="faq4" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                            <div class="accordion-body">
                                Absolutely. MailTo embeds a pixel tracker in each email. You can see per-contact open and delivery status from the Campaign Reports section, and export the data to Excel.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

